FT  27 MAY 94 / Stadium delay
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Five English first-division football clubs were yesterday granted an
extension of a year to meet the regulations for all-seater stadiums. Derby
County, Grimsby Town, Middlesbrough, Portsmouth and Sunderland must now
comply by August next year.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
