<HEADLINE>
FT  27 MAY 94 / Monks calls for union change
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The battle for full employment requires unions to change their behaviour, Mr
John Monks, general secretary of the Trades Union Congress, said yesterday.
He told the Royal Society of Arts that unions had given too little attention
to job security. 'All too often pay is at the top of the bargaining agenda
and job security effectively at the bottom,' he said.
'Some of the excessive rigidities in our labour market such as systematic
overtime, predominantly a male phenomenon, are as much the result of
employer preferences as trade union demands, but nevertheless we share the
blame.'
</TEXT>
