<HEADLINE>
FT  26 MAY 94 / International Company News: Sluggish earnings for JR East
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
East Japan Railway (JR East), the semi-privatised railway group, posted
sluggish earnings figures for the year to last March due to a decline in
revenue from its passenger operations.
Consolidated pre-tax profits fell 1.8 per cent to Y108.6bn (Dollars 1bn), on
a 0.4 per cent fall in the group's revenue to Y2,343.35bn. After-tax profits
fell 0.2 per cent to Y56.7bn.
The company said its poor performance in the railway operations eroded the
gains from sales increases in its kiosks, travel agent and real estate
leasing division.
On a non-consolidated basis, JR East posted a 0.6 per cent rise in pre-tax
profits to Y101.5bn thanks to a Y20bn fall in interest payments due to lower
interest rates. Revenues fell 0.3 per cent fall to Y1,974.35bn and after-tax
profits fell 0.4 per cent to Y56.7bn.
For the current year to next March, the company expects consolidated pre-tax
profits to remain almost flat, down 0.8 per cent to Y109.6bn, on a 6.7 per
cent rise in sales to Y2,502.5bn.
</TEXT>
