FT  26 MAY 94 / Institutions warn on housing grants
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
City investors most involved with housing associations have warned that cuts
in government housing grants could make it harder to provide private finance
to build low-cost homes for rent, according to the National Federation of
Housing Associations.
A majority of institutions contacted by the federation said they were
concerned at government plans to cut the grant rate to 55 per cent of the
cost of a new home. Several said that they were concerned that the financial
health of associations might be affected.
